1\. Describe Adam as originally created.

2\. How does man get away from sense consciousness?

3\. How are we transformed?

<span id="page_199">p. 199</span>

4\. What must we do to escape the second death?

5\. How do we realize eternal life?

6\. What is man's salvation?

7\. Explain the law of life and how it is revealed to man.

8\. Explain the effect of the cells of the body on health.

9\. What is a universal solvent?

10\. How can man cleanse his thought?

11\. What is the wisdom of Spirit?

12\. What is the secret of the demonstration of Christ?

13\. How do we become really alive?

14\. How does Jesus describe the states of consciousness of one who
passes through the change called death?

15\. What is the effect of material selfishness?

16\. How is man affected when he loses the material avenues of
expression?

17\. Define man; Spirit.

18\. What is the soul? the body?

19\. What is the goal of man?

20\. What replaces the physical body?

Lesson XIV--Jesus Christ's Atonement

1\. What is symbolically described as the Edenic stage?

2\. How does man get away from sense consciousness?

3\. Describe the results of disorder in man's relation to creation.

4\. Can man thwart the divine plan?

5\. Explain God's idea of man.

6\. What are we seeking?

<span id="page_200">p. 200</span>

7\. What is the root of the church's teaching? What part does Jesus
play?

8\. How can we understand the atonement?

9\. Explain Jesus' opening the way for all who will follow Him.

10\. How do we receive the benefits of Jesus' work?

11\. Explain the higher and the lower consciousness of Jesus Christ.

12\. Why is thought co-operation advantageous?

13\. What factor made Jesus God incarnate?

14\. Why can't we separate Jesus Christ from God?

15\. What was the process of Jesus' evolving?

16\. What words of Jesus have rung through the ages?

17\. Explain universal belief in the power of the sacred word.

18\. What does Jesus tell us to do?

19\. Define personal consciousness.

20\. How can you be yourself?

